From 221767a4cce4fd6233a29e12541dffd0d2af89f4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Jun 2026 07:33:45 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(orders): basket-as-order lifecycle (active -> paid + new
 active basket)

- Basket model: drop unique-per-user, add status (active/pending_payment/paid/
  cancelled) plus order fields (orderNumber, shipping, totals, tax, discount,
  finalPrice, transactionId, isPaid/paidAt); getOrCreate now returns the ACTIVE
  basket, add generateOrderNumber + markPaid
- All cart lookups (controller, globalData) target the active basket
- Payment: snapshot order data onto the active basket; on successful verify mark
  it paid (kept as the order record) and create a fresh empty active basket;
  failed payment leaves the basket active for retry. Order model no longer used.
- Dashboard: list the user's paid baskets as orders (with items, order number,
  jalali paid date, final price); admin dashboard counts paid baskets

Note: existing DBs must drop the legacy unique index: db.baskets.dropIndex('user_1')

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_019fhmuc7ZofnhXQGM2EDkKu
